content: Seolbong Park is located in the suburbs of Icheon city in South Korea. It is one of the most visted places in the city for spending a good weekend.

The attractions for free admission, although nothing special, can be seen that the Lichuan government has used a lot of effort to maintain the park cleanliness, but often in order to facilitate its own cleaning, after a few years, the cherry blossoms and ginkgo are over-pruned, resulting in the whole beauty is barren. This self-interest of the dumplings made it really beautiful at the time. Except for the spring cherry blossoms, the summer water dance, the autumn maple leaves, ginkgo, the winter iced lake, it is worth admiring.

Seolbong Park is located in the vicinity of Icheon City of South Korea. It is a lovely place with alot of calmness and serenity. Once can come here spend a relaxing day with family or friends. Even school kids can also come here as part of picnic activity.
The place where the Seolbong Park Ceramics Festival was held, which is good for exercise!
